Also a big shoutout to https://ourworldindata.org/ – the online publication for research and data on the world’s largest problems – and how to make progress solving them. Check out their site. It also includes a constantly updated page on the Corona Pandemic. Working together with them over the years has been a delight.

snippet.textDisplay:
I would just like to copy a comment that I made in another comment thread regarding vaccines, primarily directed at anti-vaxxers:
Vaccines do NOT cause autism. The doctor who made that statement got his medical license withdrawn and I think he himself even admitted to being in the wrong about this. Stop spreading bullshit and do your research. The common known vaccines that have been around since we were children had been researched for 20+ years before they even came into use. The swine flu shot, on the other hand, was only researched for a short amount of time before being distributed which made it a much higher risk for serious side-effects (the reason I regret taking it and will definitely not be taking the future corona vaccine for that same reason). The standard vaccines provided for newborns and toddlers should pretty much be mandatory to maintain herd immunity, and protect those who can not take the vaccines for different reasons.
